@*
    /docs/rbac — Developer reference for role-based access control.
    Documents how the three independent authorization layers (UserRole enum,
    Group → Feature → Permission, API token Bearer scopes) compose, how the
    custom MVC filters in Attributes/Require*.cs gate controllers, and how
    the NavigationViewFilter drives the Modern UI navigation.

    Source of truth: Models/, Services/PermissionService.cs, Attributes/Require*.cs,
    Filters/*FeatureGateFilter.cs, Filters/NavigationViewFilter.cs, Program.cs
    SeedRbacInitialDataAsync.
*@
@{
    const string flowPalette = """

  classDef actor fill:#1b3a5b,stroke:#1d70b8,color:#fff;
  classDef action fill:#2b3a4a,stroke:#7da3c4,color:#fff;
  classDef store fill:#3a2e57,stroke:#9579c7,color:#fff;
  classDef decision fill:#5a3a18,stroke:#d09a4a,color:#fff;
  classDef terminal fill:#1f4f2c,stroke:#52b06d,color:#fff;
  classDef deny fill:#5a1f1f,stroke:#d4534f,color:#fff;
""";

    var flowRequest = """
flowchart LR
  REQ(["HTTP request"]):::actor --> ROUTE["UseRouting"]:::action
  ROUTE --> APIM["ApiAuthenticationMiddleware<br/>matches /api/v1 or /api/products/fips"]:::action
  APIM -- bearer token --> APITOK[("ApiToken + ApiTokenPermission")]:::store
  APIM --> COOKIE["UseAuthentication<br/>Entra OIDC cookie"]:::action
  COOKIE --> ENSURE["EnsureCompassUserMiddleware<br/>upserts User, emits ClaimTypes.Role"]:::action
  ENSURE --> AUTHZ["UseAuthorization"]:::action
  AUTHZ --> NAVF["NavigationViewFilter<br/>sets ViewBag flags via IPermissionService"]:::action
  NAVF --> ATTR{{"Controller / action attributes"}}:::decision
  ATTR -- Authorize --> SIGN{{"Signed in?"}}:::decision
  SIGN -- no --> CHAL["Challenge: redirect to Entra"]:::deny
  SIGN -- yes --> GROUP{{"Require* attributes:<br/>RequireAdmin · RequireSuperAdmin · RequireCentralOpsAdmin ·<br/>RequireDesignOpsAdmin · RequireOperationConsoleUser"}}:::decision
  GROUP -- group lookup fails --> REDIR["Redirect to /Admin or /CentralOps/AccessDenied"]:::deny
  GROUP --> FGATE{{"ServiceFilter: feature-gate"}}:::decision
  FGATE -- feature off --> DASH["Redirect to /modern/dashboard"]:::deny
  FGATE --> APIPERM{{"RequireApiPermission(res, op)"}}:::decision
  APIPERM -- missing scope --> JSON["403 JSON"]:::deny
  APIPERM --> OWN{{"Imperative check<br/>CanUserEditWorkItem · CurrentUserMayEditIssue"}}:::decision
  OWN -- no --> FORBID["Forbid() / Unauthorized()"]:::deny
  OWN -- yes --> ACTION["Controller action runs"]:::terminal
""" + flowPalette;
}

<div class="developers-docs__intro govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
    <span class="govuk-caption-xl">Reference</span>
    <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl govuk-!-margin-bottom-2">RBAC &amp; authorization</h1>
    <p class="govuk-body-l govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
        How Compass decides who can do what. Three independent layers
        compose on top of Entra ID sign-in: the legacy <code>UserRole</code>
        enum, the live <em>Group &rarr; Feature &rarr; Permission</em> model
        in <code>IPermissionService</code>, and per-token Bearer scopes for
        the JSON API. This page is the developer-facing reference for all
        of it.
    </p>
</div>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="overview">Overview</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">
    Compass does not use ASP.NET Core named authorization policies
    (<code>AddPolicy("...", p =&gt; p.Require...)</code>) or custom
    <code>IAuthorizationRequirement</code> / <code>AuthorizationHandler&lt;&gt;</code>
    types. <code>Program.cs</code> has a single bare <code>AddAuthorization()</code>
    call (<code>Program.cs:316</code>) and every gating decision is made by
    one of three layers:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
    <li>
        <strong>Layer 1 &mdash; <code>UserRole</code> enum (vestigial).</strong>
        Defined at <code>Models/User.cs:53-59</code> with values
        <code>Visitor / Reporter / Admin / SuperAdmin</code>.
        Materialised as a <code>ClaimTypes.Role</code> claim by
        <code>EnsureCompassUserMiddleware</code>. Only three controller actions
        in the whole codebase use <code>[Authorize(Roles = ...)]</code>; in
        practice the enum is treated as deprecated and roles are managed
        via Groups.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Layer 2 &mdash; Group &rarr; Feature &rarr; Permission
        (the live mechanism).</strong>
        Backed by EF tables <code>Groups</code>, <code>UserGroups</code>,
        <code>Features</code>, <code>GroupFeaturePermissions</code>,
        <code>FeatureUserAllow</code>, <code>FeatureGroupAllow</code>.
        Service: <code>IPermissionService</code> (<code>Services/PermissionService.cs</code>).
        Custom MVC filters (<code>[RequireAdmin]</code>, <code>[RequireSuperAdmin]</code>,
        <code>[RequireCentralOpsAdmin]</code>, <code>[RequireDesignOpsAdmin]</code>,
        <code>[RequireOperationConsoleUser]</code>) call group lookups on
        <code>IPermissionService</code> per request.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Layer 3 &mdash; API token Bearer scopes.</strong>
        Tables <code>ApiTokens</code> + <code>ApiTokenPermissions</code>;
        <code>ApiAuthenticationMiddleware</code> matches
        <code>/api/v1/*</code> and <code>/api/products/fips/*</code>;
        actions are decorated with
        <code>[RequireApiPermission("Resource", "operation")]</code>.
        Entirely independent of the cookie-auth user roles.
    </li>
</ol>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
    <strong>There is no Entra-to-claim role mapping.</strong>
    <code>Program.cs</code> has no <code>TokenValidationParameters.RoleClaimType</code>,
    no <code>MapInboundClaims</code> override, and no
    <code>OnTokenValidated</code> handler. Adding a user to an Entra group
    has zero effect until they are also added to a Compass <code>Group</code>
    via the admin UI.
</div>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="request-flow">Authorization decision flow</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">
    The diagram below traces a single HTTP request through every
    authorization step. The same pipeline serves cookie-authenticated
    Modern UI requests and Bearer-authenticated API requests; the
    <code>ApiAuthenticationMiddleware</code> short-circuits the cookie
    flow when the path begins with <code>/api/v1</code> or
    <code>/api/products/fips</code>.
</p>

<partial name="_DataFlowDiagram" model='("rbac-request", flowRequest)' />

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="signin-flow">Sign-in and claim hydration</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">
    Sign-in is delegated to Entra ID via <code>Microsoft.Identity.Web</code>.
    The pipeline is configured in <code>Program.cs</code> as follows:
</p>

<div class="developers-data-models">
    <table class="govuk-table">
        <caption class="govuk-table__caption govuk-visually-hidden">Authentication and authorization pipeline registration</caption>
        <thead class="govuk-table__head">
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Concern</th>
                <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">File:line</th>
                <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Notes</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="govuk-table__body">
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header"><code>AddAuthentication(...).AddMicrosoftIdentityWebApp(...)</code></th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>Program.cs:301-302</code></td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Cookie scheme with Entra OIDC challenge.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header"><code>AddAuthorization()</code></th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>Program.cs:316</code></td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">No policies registered. All gating is via custom filters.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header">Global navigation filter</th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>Program.cs:307</code></td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Registers <code>NavigationViewFilter</code> as a global MVC filter.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header"><code>ApiAuthenticationMiddleware</code></th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>Program.cs:672</code></td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Runs <strong>before</strong> cookie auth; resolves Bearer tokens.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header"><code>UseAuthentication</code></th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>Program.cs:675</code></td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Cookie / OIDC.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header"><code>EnsureCompassUserMiddleware</code></th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>Program.cs:676</code></td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Upserts the local <code>User</code> row and appends a <code>ClaimTypes.Role</code> claim derived from <code>User.Role</code>.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header"><code>UseAuthorization</code></th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>Program.cs:677</code></td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Runs the controller / action authorization filters.</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>

<p class="govuk-body">
    <code>EnsureCompassUserMiddleware</code> (<code>Middlewares/EnsureCompassUserMiddleware.cs</code>)
    is the only producer of <code>ClaimTypes.Role</code>. It maps the
    <code>UserRole</code> enum:
</p>

```92:99:Middlewares/EnsureCompassUserMiddleware.cs
var roleClaimValue = user.Role switch
{
    UserRole.Admin => "Admin",
    UserRole.SuperAdmin => "SuperAdmin",
    UserRole.Reporter => "Reporter",
    UserRole.Visitor => "Visitor",
    _ => "Visitor"
};
```

<p class="govuk-body">
    New users default to <code>UserRole.Visitor</code>. The admin UI does
    not expose a way to mutate <code>User.Role</code>; the legacy edit
    action (<code>Controllers/AdminController.cs:751-761</code>) explicitly
    preserves the existing value with the comment
    &ldquo;<em>roles are managed through groups in UserManagement</em>&rdquo;.
</p>

<hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break--visible">

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="roles-groups">Roles, groups and features</h2>

