            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header"><code>[RequireOperationConsoleUser]</code> &mdash; <code>Attributes/RequireOperationConsoleUserAttribute.cs</code></th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Super admin, <code>Central Operations Admin</code>, OR <code>Admin</code> group.</td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Redirect to <code>/CentralOps/AccessDenied</code>.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header"><code>[RequireApiPermission(resource, op)]</code> &mdash; <code>Attributes/RequireApiPermissionAttribute.cs</code></th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Bearer token with matching <code>ApiTokenPermission</code>. See <a class="govuk-link" href="#api-tokens">API tokens</a>.</td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>401</code> JSON (no token) or <code>403</code> JSON (insufficient scope).</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header"><code>[ServiceFilter(typeof(*FeatureGateFilter))]</code></th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Anyone if the feature is <code>OnForAll</code>; specific users / groups if <code>OnForSome</code>.</td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">Redirect to <code>/modern/dashboard</code>.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="govuk-table__row">
                <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header"><code>[RequireFeaturePermission(code, type)]</code></th>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">User in a group that owns the matching <code>GroupFeaturePermission</code>.</td>
                <td class="govuk-table__cell">JSON <code>401</code> / <code>403</code>. <strong>Defined but not used anywhere</strong> &mdash; see <a class="govuk-link" href="#anomalies">anomalies</a>.</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="ipermissionservice"><code>IPermissionService</code></h3>
<p class="govuk-body">
    The single service that every gate calls into.
    <code>Services/IPermissionService.cs</code>:
</p>

```5:18:Services/IPermissionService.cs
public interface IPermissionService
{
    Task<bool> HasPermissionAsync(string userEmail, string featureCode, PermissionType permission);
    Task<bool> IsSuperAdminAsync(string userEmail);
    Task<bool> IsCentralOperationsAdminOrSuperAdminAsync(string userEmail);
    Task<bool> IsOperationConsoleUserAsync(string userEmail);
    Task<bool> IsInGroupAsync(string userEmail, string groupName);
    Task<List<string>> GetUserGroupsAsync(string userEmail);
    Task<List<PermissionType>> GetUserPermissionsForFeatureAsync(string userEmail, string featureCode);
    Task<User?> GetOrCreateUserAsync(string email, string? name = null);
}
```

<p class="govuk-body">
    Two implicit bypasses live inside <code>HasPermissionAsync</code>
    (<code>Services/PermissionService.cs:62-100</code>): super admin always
    returns <code>true</code> (line 74), and Central Operations Admin
    always returns <code>true</code> (line 89). Otherwise the query joins
    <code>GroupFeaturePermissions</code> on the user&rsquo;s groups and
    insists <code>Feature.AccessMode != FeatureAccessMode.Off</code>.
</p>

