<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="api-tokens">API token authentication</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">
    Bearer-token auth is layered <strong>before</strong> cookie auth in
    the middleware pipeline (<code>Program.cs:672</code> vs <code>675</code>),
    so the JSON API does not need a signed-in user. Cookie-authenticated
    legacy API controllers (<code>Api/StaffController</code>,
    <code>Api/EntitiesController</code>, <code>Api/V1/ChatbotController</code>)
    use <code>[Authorize]</code> only and inherit user identity through the
    cookie scheme.
</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="token-model">Token model</h3>
<p class="govuk-body">
    <code>ApiToken</code> (<code>Models/ApiToken.cs</code>) carries the
    metadata (name, secret, created-by, status, expiry, last-used) and a
    collection of <code>ApiTokenPermission</code> rows
    (<code>Models/ApiTokenPermission.cs</code>) with four boolean columns
    per resource: <code>CanRead</code>, <code>CanCreate</code>,
    <code>CanUpdate</code>, <code>CanDelete</code>.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
    Tokens are minted as <code>cps_&lt;base64&gt;</code>
    (<code>Services/ApiTokenService.cs:41-60</code>) and stored verbatim.
    Validation:
</p>

```193:200:Services/ApiTokenService.cs
return operation.ToLower() switch
{
    "read" or "get" => permission.CanRead,
    "create" or "post" => permission.CanCreate,
    "update" or "put" or "patch" => permission.CanUpdate,
    "delete" => permission.CanDelete,
    _ => false
};
```

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="token-resources">Resource catalogue</h3>
<p class="govuk-body">
    The permission UI iterates a fixed array at
    <code>Controllers/Modern/ModernAdminController.cs:3333-3341</code>:
</p>

```3333:3341:Controllers/Modern/ModernAdminController.cs
private static readonly string[] ApiTokenResources = new[]
{
    "Risks", "Issues", "Actions", "Milestones", "PerformanceMetrics",
    "EnterpriseMetrics", "FunctionalStandards", "AccessibilityIssues",
    "SurveysAdmin", "UserSatisfactionQuestions", "UserSatisfactionResponses", "DdtStandards",
    "ServiceRegister",
    "CmsAccessRequests",
    "AdminLookups"
};
```

<p class="govuk-body">
    Each <code>Api/V1/*Controller</code> decorates its actions with the
    matching <code>[RequireApiPermission("&lt;resource&gt;", "&lt;operation&gt;")]</code>.
    <code>DdtStandardsController</code> is an exception &mdash; its 12 read
    endpoints are <code>[AllowAnonymous]</code> on purpose (the controller
    enforces <code>Where(s =&gt; s.IsPublished &amp;&amp; s.Stage == "Published")</code>
    on every query), and only the write endpoints require
    <code>"DdtStandards"</code> token scopes.
</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="api-middleware">Middleware behaviour</h3>
<p class="govuk-body">
    <code>ApiAuthenticationMiddleware</code> (lines 20-22) matches the path:
</p>

```20:22:Middlewares/ApiAuthenticationMiddleware.cs
var isApiV1 = context.Request.Path.StartsWithSegments("/api/v1");
var isFipsProductLookups = context.Request.Path.StartsWithSegments("/api/products/fips");
if (!isApiV1 && !isFipsProductLookups)
```

<p class="govuk-body">
    For matching paths it requires an <code>Authorization: Bearer
    cps_...</code> header, looks up the token via
    <code>IApiTokenService.GetByTokenAsync</code>, stores it in
    <code>HttpContext.Items["ApiToken"]</code> (line 85) and bumps
    <code>LastUsedAt</code> (line 88). The
    <code>[RequireApiPermission]</code> filter reads
    <code>HttpContext.Items["ApiToken"]</code> back out and delegates to
    <code>IApiTokenService.ValidatePermission</code>.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
    Every API call is logged by <code>ApiLoggingMiddleware</code>
    (registered at <code>Program.cs:673</code>) into <code>ApiRequestLog</code>.
    The <code>/health</code> endpoint is exempted at
    <code>ApiAuthenticationMiddleware.cs:29</code>.
</p>

