<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="seeding">Seeding</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">
    Initial RBAC data is created by <code>SeedRbacInitialDataAsync</code>
    in <code>Program.cs:979-1436</code>, called from <code>Program.cs:756</code>.
    Pre-condition: <code>Authentication:SuperAdminEmail</code> in
    configuration (read at <code>Program.cs:720</code>). The seeder no-ops
    if the <code>Super admin</code> group already exists.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">What is seeded:</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>The super-admin <code>User</code> row (lines 1002-1023).</li>
    <li><code>Super admin</code> group with <code>IsSystemGroup = true</code> (lines 1025-1041) and the super-admin user as a member.</li>
    <li><code>Central Operations Admin</code> group with <code>IsSystemGroup = true</code> (lines 1065-1085) and the super-admin user as a member.</li>
    <li>Ten foundational features (<code>delivery_reporting</code>, <code>risks</code>, <code>issues</code>, <code>actions</code>, <code>objectives</code>, <code>projects</code>, <code>accessibility</code>, <code>surveys</code>, <code>enterprise_reporting</code>, <code>group_management</code>) plus all four <code>PermissionType</code> rows on each for <code>Central Operations Admin</code>.</li>
    <li><code>ddt_standards</code>, <code>demand</code>, <code>standards</code>, <code>fips</code> features.</li>
    <li><code>Standard Owners</code>, <code>Standard Approvers</code>, <code>Standard Publishers</code> groups plus their <code>ddt_standards</code> permissions.</li>
</ul>

<p class="govuk-body">What is <strong>not</strong> seeded:</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li><code>raid</code> and <code>ddr</code> features &mdash; <code>IGlobalFeatureToggleService</code> falls back to <code>ApplicationFeatureToggleDefinition.All</code> defaults if the DB row is missing.</li>
    <li><code>Standards Managers</code>, <code>Admin</code> (group), <code>Design Operations</code>, <code>HOP</code>, <code>Demand Management</code>, <code>Demand Triage</code> &mdash; create via the admin UI before any of the dependent attributes will resolve.</li>
</ul>

