<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="cookbook">Cookbook</h2>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="cookbook-controller">Gate a new Modern controller</h3>
<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
    <li>Add <code>[Authorize]</code> at the class level (always).</li>
    <li>Pick the strictest existing attribute that fits:
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>Most Modern user-facing controllers: <code>[Authorize]</code> alone is fine and per-record gating goes inside the service.</li>
            <li>Admin hub controllers: <code>[Authorize] [RequireAdmin]</code>.</li>
            <li>Destructive global actions: method-level <code>[RequireSuperAdmin]</code>.</li>
            <li>Operations hub: <code>[Authorize] [RequireOperationConsoleUser]</code>.</li>
            <li>Anything FIPS / asset-management: <code>[Authorize] [RequireDesignOpsAdmin]</code>.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>If the controller belongs to a toggled feature area, add the matching <code>[ServiceFilter(typeof(*FeatureGateFilter))]</code>.</li>
    <li>For per-record write actions, wrap with the same pattern as <code>EnsureUserCanEditWorkAsync</code> &mdash; a private helper that returns <code>IActionResult?</code> (<code>null</code> = allowed, otherwise <code>Forbid()</code> / <code>Unauthorized()</code>).</li>
    <li>If the action returns a partial or sets bag values consumed by a view, set a <code>ViewBag.Can*</code> flag rather than duplicating the check in Razor.</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="cookbook-api">Add a new API endpoint</h3>
<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
    <li>Place the controller under <code>Controllers/Api/V1/</code>.</li>
    <li>Decorate the action with <code>[RequireApiPermission("&lt;Resource&gt;", "&lt;operation&gt;")]</code> using a resource name that is already in <code>ApiTokenResources</code>. If you need a new resource, add it to <code>ApiTokenResources</code> at <code>ModernAdminController.cs:3333-3341</code> so admins can grant it on the token-permissions screen.</li>
    <li>Operations are case-insensitive strings; stick to <code>"read" / "create" / "update" / "delete"</code> (the validator also accepts <code>"get" / "post" / "put" / "patch"</code>).</li>
    <li>Do <strong>not</strong> add <code>[Authorize]</code> &mdash; the middleware is Bearer-only for <code>/api/v1/*</code>.</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m" id="cookbook-feature">Gate the UI on a feature toggle</h3>
<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
    <li>Add a constant to <code>Models/FeatureCodes.cs</code>.</li>
    <li>Seed a <code>Feature</code> row in <code>Program.cs &gt; SeedRbacInitialDataAsync</code> with an explicit <code>AccessMode</code>.</li>
    <li>Build a <code>*FeatureGateFilter</code> mirroring the existing four in <code>Filters/</code> and register it as <code>Scoped</code> at <code>Program.cs:433-436</code>.</li>
    <li>Add the flag to <code>NavigationViewFilter.cs</code> if it should drive nav visibility, and consume it in <code>Views/Modern/Shared/_Navigation.cshtml</code> or the relevant sub-nav partial.</li>
    <li>Decorate the controller with <code>[ServiceFilter(typeof(YourFilter))]</code>.</li>
</ol>

